//Matsuo Bashō (松尾 芭蕉, 1644–1694), Furu ike ya (Curtis Hidden Page, trans.)
#!ctsdata
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.page:1#A lonely pond in age-old stillness sleeps . . .
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.page:2#Apart, unstirred by sound or motion . . . till
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.page:3#Suddenly into it a lithe frog leaps.

