urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.saijiki:1#elegance
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.saijiki:2#springtime
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.saijiki:3#vulgarity

//Matsuo Bashō (松尾 芭蕉, 1644–1694), Furu ike ya (Alfred H. Marks, trans.)
#!ctsdata
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.marks:1#There once was a curious frog
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.marks:2#Who sat by a pond on a log
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.marks:3#And, to see what resulted,
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.marks:4#In the pond catapulted
urn:cts:fuMisc:basho.kawazu.marks:5#With a water-noise heard round the bog.

